<item>
            <title>[SOLR-15961] PKIAuthenticationPlugin.parseCipher is too lenient, causing unnecessary authentication errors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15961</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It will accept an input &lt;tt&gt;SolrAuth&lt;/tt&gt; header as valid with an invalid/outdated public key as long as the output of &lt;tt&gt;CryptoKeys.decryptRSA&lt;/tt&gt; ends with a space followed by a number. It will interpret the number as a (very small) timestamp, which will cause the request to fail with 401, instead of re-fetching the public key from the remote host.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13425456">SOLR-15961</key>
